# Make Agent Webhook Streaming Work for Mux Events

## Question

Found during the [2026-07-13 E2E run](./docs/e2e-mux-manual-run-2026-07-13.svx): `joelclaw webhook subscribe mux asset.ready --stream` registers a subscription (ADR-0185 Redis keys land) that nothing ever dispatches — `packages/system-bus/src/inngest/functions/webhook-subscription-dispatch.ts` only triggers on `github/workflow_run.completed`. The CLI silently accepts subscriptions for every provider the gateway knows. Fix: generalize dispatch so session subscriptions deliver for `mux/*` (and, when it exists, `deepgram/*`) — either an Inngest wildcard-trigger dispatcher or per-provider trigger registration; decide which while implementing, and either constrain the CLI to dispatchable providers or make dispatch universal. This is the agent monitoring surface for the agentic Loom vision — "agents publish and watch it land" needs streamed events, not API polling. Resolved when `joelclaw webhook subscribe mux asset.ready --stream` prints a real event during a video publish.

## Answer

Resolved 2026-07-13 (pi worker Chuffed Jason + steering session). `webhook-subscription-dispatch-generic.ts`: one generic dispatcher, explicit 8-event trigger list for `mux/*` (Inngest 3.54.2 has no wildcard triggers — verified in node_modules); adding deepgram later is one line in `WEBHOOK_PROVIDER_NAMES`. Registered on BOTH host and cluster indexes — the same-day Front incident proved cluster-only registration silently never runs on flagg. **Live-verified**: `joelclaw webhook subscribe mux asset.ready --stream` printed the matched event seconds after a signed synthetic `video.asset.ready` hit `hooks.joelclaw.com`. Committed as `1780ed61`.

**Load-bearing side discovery:** the host app's Inngest registry sync had been failing for a while ("At least one function is invalid", 58 warnings in the worker err log) — meaning NO newly added function was reaching the Inngest server, including `joelclaw-video-hello` and everything phase 1 would add. Bisected to `voice-call-judge.ts` (another session's uncommitted work): its `idempotency` used JS `??` inside what must be a CEL expression. Fixed in place to `has(event.data.timestamp) ? string(event.data.timestamp) : ""` — the fix lives in that session's still-uncommitted file and rides their commit. Registry now syncs "Successfully registered" with all 147 host functions.
